लुच्चा luchchā _a_ and _mc_ vagrant (person), vagabond = लफ़ंगा q. v. 
लुटना luṭ·nā _vt_ to be robbed; घर लुट गया the house was robbed; गाड़ी में मुसाफ़िर लुटे passengers in the train have been robbed. 
लुटाना luṭānā _vt_ to squander: रुपया, बचत ~ -- money, savings; व्यापारी ने सारा माल सस्ते दामों लुटा दिया the businessman gave away the entire goods at a cheap price. 
